{"parse":{"title":"Superordinate goals","pageid":7318182,"revid":763799651,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Psychology\" title=\"Psychology\">psychology</a>, <b>superordinate goals</b> refer to goals that require the cooperation of two or more people or groups to achieve, which usually results in rewards to the groups.\n<a href=\"/wiki/Muzafer_Sherif\" title=\"Muzafer Sherif\">Muzafer Sherif</a> (1954) performed a study at a camp involving two groups of boys, the Eagles and the Rattlers, that were in opposition to one another in a <a href=\"/wiki/Zero-sum\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Zero-sum\">zero-sum</a> situation.  The opposing groups had strong negative feelings towards each other, resulting in hostile actions such as 'garbage wars'.\n</p><p>Simple noncompetitive interactions between groups was not enough to alter the hostile opposition of one another.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Sherif was able to successfully bring these two groups together by using superordinate goals, such as solving the problems of a breakdown of the water supply and the breakdown of a food delivery truck. The cumulative effect of these incidents was friendship formation across group boundaries. On the last day, both groups elected to ride home together on the same bus.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Superordinate_goals&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Gaertner, Samuel L.; Dovidio, John F. (2000). \"Reducing Intergroup Conflict: From Superordinate Goals to Decategorization, Recategorization, and Mutual Differentiation\". <i>Group Dynamics: Theory, Research, and Practice</i>. <b>4</b> (1): 98\u2013114.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Group+Dynamics%3A+Theory%2C+Research%2C+and+Practice&amp;rft.atitle=Reducing+Intergroup+Conflict%3A+From+Superordinate+Goals+to+Decategorization%2C+Recategorization%2C+and+Mutual+Differentiation&amp;rft.volume=4&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=98-114&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.aulast=Gaertner&amp;rft.aufirst=Samuel+L.&amp;rft.au=Dovidio%2C+John+F.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASuperordinate+goals\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<ul><li>Sherif, M., Harvey, O.J., White, B.J., Hood, W.R., &amp; Sherif, C.W.  (1961) <i>Intergroup Conflict and Co-operation: The Robbers Cave Experiment</i>.  Norman, OK: University of Oklahoma Book Exchange.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Superordinate_goals&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Psi2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Psi2.svg/30px-Psi2.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Psi2.svg/45px-Psi2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Psi2.svg/60px-Psi2.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"100\" data-file-height=\"100\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/w